      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//forester/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>7</fr:month>
              <fr:day>20</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>12041</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">//forester/jms-0067</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-0067.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Forester 2.2 › flexible transclusion options"><fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-005V.xml" title="Forester 2.2" addr="//forester/jms-005V" type="local">Forester 2.2</fr:link> › flexible transclusion options</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>This release replaces the old <fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude*]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude@]]></fr:code> commands with a more flexible transclusion configuration mechanism using the support for fluid binding introduced in <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-005O.xml" title="Forester 2.1" addr="//forester/jms-005O" type="local">Forester 2.1</fr:link>. A basic transclusion with the default options is done in the same way as before:</fr:p>
            <fr:pre><![CDATA[\transclude{jms-0005}]]></fr:pre>
            <fr:p>The behavior of transclusion is, however, configurable by several globally allocated fluid bindings as depicted in the <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-0069.xml" title="Transclusion options" addr="//forester/jms-0069" type="local">table below</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//forester/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:anchor>8442</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">//forester/jms-0069</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-0069.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Transclusion options">Transclusion options</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Table</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
  <html:table xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  
  
  <html:tr xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
  <html:th xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Fluid Binding</html:th>

    
  <html:th xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Default</html:th>

    
  <html:th xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Meaning</html:th>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>title</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:em>(none)</fr:em></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">To override the tree's title during transclusion.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>toc</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:code>true</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Show the tree in the table of contents.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>expanded</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:code>true</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Whether the tree is expanded or not.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>heading</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:code>true</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">If set to <fr:code>false</fr:code>, the tree's contents will be inlined.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>metadata</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:code>false</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Show in a tree's heading.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

  
  <html:tr xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude/]]>numbered</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:code>true</fr:code></html:td>

    
  <html:td xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Whether the tree is displayed with a number or not, transitively on subtrees.</html:td>

  </html:tr>

</html:table>
<fr:p>It is possible to achieve undesirable results by combining these options in undesirable ways; it is up to you to use them correctly.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
